  Publisher of Cross River Watch, Agba Jalingo, has finally been released from detention after perfecting his bail condition on Monday. Jalingo was arrested on the orders of Cross River State governor, Ben Ayade, after he raised questions on the whereabouts of N500m meant for the establishment of Cross River Microfinance Bank. He was detained thereafter arbitrarily for over four months with his fundamental human rights grossly violated during the period. More to comeâ€¦